  "local_port": 32972,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best coffee shops with Wi-Fi in San Francisco for evening work?",
  "response": "San Francisco is home to a vibrant coffee scene with numerous spots that cater to evening workers looking for a comfortable environment with reliable Wi-Fi. Here are some of the best coffee shops in San Francisco for evening work:\n\n### 1. **Blue Bottle Coffee**\n- **Locations:** Multiple across SF, including the **Mint Plaza** and **Telegraph Hill**.\n- **Hours:** Many locations stay open until 7 PM or later.\n- **Highlights:** Known for high-quality coffee and minimalist ambiance. Some locations offer ample seating and power outlets, making them ideal for working into the evening.\n\n### 2. **Sightglass Coffee**\n- **Address:** 270 7th Street, San Francisco, CA 94103\n- **Hours:** Typically open until 6 PM or later, depending on the location.\n- **Highlights:** Spacious interiors with industrial-chic d\u00e9cor, free Wi-Fi, and plenty of natural light. Great for those who prefer a lively atmosphere while working.\n\n### 3. **Philz Coffee**\n- **Locations:** Multiple, including the popular **Mission District** and **Hayes Valley**.\n- **Hours:** Many stores remain open until 8 PM or later.\n- **Highlights:** Famous for customized drip coffee. Comfortable seating and a community-oriented vibe make it a favorite among freelancers and remote workers.\n\n### 4. **The Mill**\n- **Address:** 736 Divisadero Street, San Francisco, CA 94117\n- **Hours:** Open until 6 PM, but some special events or extended hours may apply.\n- **Highlights:** Combines excellent coffee with artisanal toast and pastries. Stylish space with good Wi-Fi, ideal for early evening work sessions.\n\n### 5. **Caffe Trieste**\n- **Address:** 601 Vallejo Street, San Francisco, CA 94133\n- **Hours:** Open until 10 PM on weekdays.\n- **Highlights:** A historic North Beach caf\u00e9 known for its cozy ambiance, rich coffee, and live music nights. Offers a unique setting for evening work with a touch of local culture.\n\n### 6. **Ritual Coffee Roasters**\n- **Locations:** Several, including **Mission District** and **NHA**.\n- **Hours:** Vary by location, with some open until 7 PM or later.\n- **Highlights:** Specialty coffee with a focus on sustainability. Modern interiors, reliable Wi-Fi, and plenty of seating make it conducive for productivity.\n\n### 7. **Four Barrel Coffee**\n- **Address:** 375 Valencia Street, San Francisco, CA 94103\n- **Hours:** Open until 6 PM or later, depending on the day.\n- **Highlights:** Rustic d\u00e9cor with a laid-back atmosphere. Offers strong Wi-Fi and a variety of coffee blends, perfect for sustained evening work.\n\n### 8. **Saint Frank Coffee**\n- **Address:** 2340 Polk Street, San Francisco, CA 94109\n- **Hours:** Typically open until 6 PM, but check specific locations for extended hours.\n- **Highlights:** Sleek and modern interior with a focus on quality coffee sourcing. Comfortable spaces and dependable internet make it suitable for late-day tasks.\n\n### 9. **Coffee Bar**\n- **Address:** 1700 California Street, San Francisco, CA 94109\n- **Hours:** Open until 6 PM or later.\n- **Highlights:** Offers a quiet environment with ample seating and reliable Wi-Fi. Ideal for those seeking a more subdued place to work in the evening.\n\n### 10. **Philz Santa Barbara Street**\n- **Address:** 1490 14th Street, San Francisco, CA 94103\n- **Hours:** Often open until 8 PM on weekdays.\n- **Highlights:** A branch of the popular Philz chain, this location provides a cozy atmosphere with plenty of outlets and strong Wi-Fi, perfect for evening productivity.\n\n---\n\n**Tips for Evening Work at Coffee Shops:**\n- **Check Hours in Advance:** Hours can vary, especially on weekends or holidays, so it\u2019s a good idea to verify current operating hours before heading out.\n- **Consider Noise Levels:** Some cafes are livelier in the evenings, which can be either inspiring or distracting depending on your work style.\n- **Availability of Power Outlets:** If you need to charge your devices, look for places that offer plenty of accessible outlets.\n- **Menu Offerings:** Ensure the caf\u00e9 serves food or snacks if you plan to work through dinner time.\n\nThese coffee shops offer a blend of excellent coffee, conducive work environments, and reliable Wi-Fi, making them ideal choices for evening work sessions in San Francisco. Whether you prefer a bustling atmosphere or a quiet nook, you're likely to find a spot that fits your needs.",
